8\">:</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"src-anchor-lineno\">333229</span><span class=\"src-anchor-linecode\"><span style=\"--shiki-light:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#9ECBFF\">            `**Session database** (database: \"session\", the default):</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"src-anchor-lineno\">333230</span><span class=\"src-anchor-linecode\"><span style=\"--shiki-light:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#9ECBFF\">The per-session database persists across the session but is isolated from other sessions.</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"src-anchor-lineno\">333231</span><span class=\"src-anchor-linecode\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"src-anchor-lineno\">333232</span><span class=\"src-anchor-linecode\"><span style=\"--shiki-light:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#9ECBFF\">**When to use SQL vs plan.md:**</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"src-anchor-lineno\">333233</span><span class=\"src-anchor-linecode\"><span style=\"--shiki-light:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#9ECBFF\">- Use plan.md for prose: problem statements, approach notes, high-level planning</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"src-anchor-lineno\">333234</span><span class=\"src-anchor-linecode\"><span style=\"--shiki-light:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#9ECBFF\">- Use SQL for operational data: todo lists, test cases, batch items, status tracking</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"src-anchor-lineno\">333235</span><span class=\"src-anchor-linecode\"></span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"src-anchor-lineno\">333236</span><span class=\"src-anchor-linecode\"><span style=\"--shiki-light:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#9ECBFF\">**Pre-existing tables (ready to use):**</span></span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"src-anchor-lineno\">333237</span><span class=\"src-anchor-linecode\"><span style=\"--shiki-light:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#9ECBFF\">- </span><span style=\"--shiki-light:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#